        "description": {
            "chat": "",
            "unidentified": "",
            "value": "<p>Gnawing worms materialize within the flesh of the target creature, dealing [[/r 4d6 #piercing]] piercing damage and [[/r 1d6 #persistent piercing]] persistent piercing damage. If the target is a non-skeletal corporeal undead creature, you deal an extra [[/r 2d6 #extra persistent piercing]] persistent piercing damage. The target must attempt a Fortitude save.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The worms writhe away harmlessly and the target takes no damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The target takes full initial damage but no persistent damage, and the spell ends immediately.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The target takes full initial and persistent damage and is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Flat-Footed]{Flat-Footed} due to the pain for as long as it takes persistent damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but the target takes double the initial damage and is also @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Slowed]{Slowed} 1 by the pain for as long as it takes persistent damage.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Heightened (+2)</strong>: The initial and persistent damage increase by 2d6 and 1d6, respectively</p>"
